	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I went to the island last night to help a friend and his partner survive helping Willowisps.  They were both Erudites, one a level 9 Wizard, the other a level 7 Enchanter.  I'm a level 14 Druid (so of course we weren't groupped, I just healed and buffed).  Well, it was about mid day (I didn't think to check the time) and I was healling after loosing half my life and some mana when three 'wisps attacked me at once.  As I was sitting and mediating I read the text &quot;an island madman begins to cast a spell&quot;.  He began to cast a few times before I saw where he was - down the ridge toward the water (we were near the top of the dead volcano).  At that point he starts to attack me with Druid spells.  The moment I start to attack back, he yells &quot;Guards! Guards! Help me!&quot;  With the help of my friends we kill him.  I cast one heal spell on myself and the I hear &quot;An island madman says 'Halflings like you desire to die'&quot; or something like that.  I look around to see the second madman come from toward the center of the crator who walked past the others to get to me.  He was not a caster and he too shouted for the guards.  By this point I was down to less than one health bubble and little mana.  With all three of us hitting  him, we despatched him when I only had about 10 hit points left.  The next day (Norrath day) I checked the time and - like I expected - it was 12 noon.  I waited a short while and then I heard &quot;An island madman begins to cast a spell&quot;.  He was another Druid but we - and another person - killed him easily.  He again had come from the the direction of the water.  I walked around looking for the second one I was sure would spawn and he did - again from the direction of the crator.  He /con'ed risky blue to me though he was taken down easily.  When the first madman attacked, there was no one else beside the three of us on the island and we were not hunting any animals, just Willowisps.  Though I didn't get time to investigate further, they may spawn at a certain time since I think they did around noon both days.  Also I found it odd after reading others' notes that both first spawns were Druids and they went after me right away.  My friends said they had hunted on the island for awhile and never had been attacked by a madman and they still weren't when I was there.  Even when they were dishing out more damage due to spells, the madmen still continued to target me.  My first guess - since my first madman encounter was a Druid - was that he was a member of the Unkempt Druids and part of a quest - since the day before I had lost faction with the Unkempt Druids, hence why he just attacked me.  I could be just grasping for JumJum stalks here but maybe there is something more.  Now that I hear there are other class madmen, I don't know.  Also, the night between madmen attacks, I was attacked by a fire elemental who avoiding hitting my friends and they had never seen one before.  The elemental also shouted before he attacked &quot;Time to die Loadhan&quot; and &quot;Druids like you are an insult to all of Norrath&quot;.  I found this odd since I have never encountered a creature who called me by name before it attacked me.  Just wondering what this is all about.<BR>
<BR>
Loadhan - E. Marr
				</font>
			</td>

